The paper deals with compression of 3D point cloud attributes, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves a family of nested partitions represented by a tree, which is a common data structure in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also mentions the use of eigenvectors, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and linear algebra (cs.LG).
